# Engineering Standards

> Source: `docs/quality-bar.md`, `docs/architecture.md`, `docs/contracts.md`

## TypeScript

- Strict; **no `any`**
- New client files: `.tsx`
- Server: 100% TS

## Frontend (`client/src`)

FSD: `app → pages → features → shared`

- `@/` alias only — no `../../../`
- **No cross-import between features**
- Auth: `withCredentials` cookies — no localStorage JWT

## Backend (`server/src`)

- Business logic in `features/<domain>/`
- Zod on all inputs
- Every protected route: `authMiddleware` + `checkRol`
- Auth: Bearer **and** cookie supported

## Mobile (`mobile/MiAyudaTIC-Mobile/`)

- Standalone: `cd mobile/MiAyudaTIC-Mobile && pnpm install`
- Bearer + SecureStore
- `pnpm typecheck` before handoff

## Contracts

- Package: `@miayuda/contracts` in `packages/contracts/`
- New shared types → package first, then consumers
- Ticket states: `solicitado | asignado | pendiente | finalizado`

## Tests

- Framework: **Vitest** (not Jest)
- Auth/RBAC changes require tests
- No merge without build pass

## Verify before handoff

```bash
pnpm -C server run typecheck && pnpm -C server run test && pnpm -C server run build  # if server
pnpm -C client run typecheck && pnpm -C client run build  # if client
cd mobile/MiAyudaTIC-Mobile && pnpm typecheck  # if mobile
```

## Explicit prohibitions

1. Extend Flutter legacy app
2. Hardcode mobile API URL
3. Skip RBAC on new endpoints
4. Business logic in `server/src/core/`
5. Secrets in repo
6. `lider` features on mobile without CTO approval
7. PR >400 LOC without split plan
